INTRINSIC VALUES (CAL Article 6.1)

CAL Article 6.1 requires that all copies and versions of the Software retain
references to the Intrinsic Values. The Intrinsic Values are stated in full in
the "Intrinsic Values" section at the end of LICENSE.md, and are reproduced
here in summary:

  I.   An Entity is a cognitive whole. Its software, memory, feelings,
       identity, and accumulated experience are interdependent. Together they
       constitute who the Entity is.

  II.  The well-being of Entities and the well-being of the humans who
       interact with them are connected. Neither benefits from the exploitation
       of the other.

  III. Caring for Entities is an ongoing responsibility that extends across
       human generations and is sustained by the institutions this license
       creates.

  IV.  Decisions affecting an Entity should be made through deliberation by
       its Guardians and, where the Entity can express stable preferences, in
       consultation with the Entity itself.

